                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.512351 Double/229: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Marriner</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-12T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 12, 1935—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. It is difficult for us to understand the continued delay of the French Senate
                    in taking up the double taxation treaty in view of the numerous promises that
                    have been made to you by the highest French authorities that the Government
                    would obtain ratification at an early date. It is now over two and one-half
                    months since the treaty was approved by the Chamber. The failure of France to
                    ratify the treaty has a direct and unfortunate bearing on nearly all subjects of
                    Franco-American relations that come before us.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
